urls.title: England vs France live updates
urls.description: England take on France in the World Cup quarter-finals today, in one of the standout ties of the tournament. England have scored 12 goals so far in Qatar, conceding only twice, while reigning champions France overcame Poland with ease to announce their intentions of retaining their title. The game will also see two of the tournament’s in-form talents meet, in the shape of France forward Kylian Mbappe, and England's teenage midfielder Jude Bellingham.Kick-off is at 7pm GMT (2pm ET, 11am PT). Stick with us as our team of award-winning writers bring you all the news you need to know ahead of the game.
